I just found the perfect sock fanatic page, which means that I'm in heaven now.

http://www.sock-dreams.com/_shop/edit/index.php

God I have been browsing through those pages for hours and letting myself dream.  The best part is that they are really cheap and they ship to Iceland, wooooo.  I have selected 6 pairs of thigh high striped and fence net stockings for only $38!!

Now I need to go and stand before G and his credit card with my best puppy eyes for about an hour! :p

Hmmmmmmm

After 5 washes the beautiful blue color has faded considerably and my hair is quite multicolored.  On top it is blonde, some of the tips are still rather dark blue, the underside is sort of greyish and the rest of the hair is a mixture of light blue, bluegreen and silver, seriously fucking strange looking.

I was going to post a pic but my webcam was being a cunt as always and refused to comply, perhaps it will feel better tomorrow.

Since I don't really have money to order some blue from Special Effects, hair color recomended to me by , and I'm not sure being a rainbow suites me, I may just dye it dark brown or black very soon, it all depends on when I lose my patience. ;)

Oh and one other thing, Stargazer's Royal Blue sucks balls!

Every Tuesday my living room get's taken over by a bunch of RPG geeks playing MERP.  Tonight I will join them. B)

I haven't role-played for ages, some 7 years I think.  It will be interesting to try again, even though I'm only covering for one of the players that can't make it tonight.

I'm in a surprisingly good mood today.  I have been smiling and giggling like a maniac all morning, for whatever reason.
It's probably because it's my birthday tomorrow.  I wasn't really going to do anything to celibrate that, but my friends changed that.  I'm going out with them tonight and have a birthday party (just family...and cakes!) tomorrow and on sunday.

Quite the busy weekend by my standards.

Note to self:  Stop being so scared of throwing things away, you are never going to wear them anyway.

My role yesterday and today is that of a chemistry teacher.  Been teaching my friend organic chemistry for a test she has tomorrow and she finally "got it" yesterday I think.  I just hope she passes this test because it's her last chance to do so.

We are both a bit insane, so studying together usually ends up in some serious silliness.  The hydra camp will be filled with insane chemistry, coke, coffee and cakes today!  
I just hope my flatmate will handle it. :p

My patience for everything is running very thin these days and I find myself snapping at some very minor things that I would usually just laugh at.
I don't like this at all! :\

It's just too goddamn hot here at the moment.  The temperature should not go up to 90 F (30 C) here at all like it did yesterday!  Today was no better.  Gaaaahhhhh, I'm not made for heat, I want cold cold cold cold cold, and that NOW!!

There have been a lot of people posting here that I don't know, not anonymous posters, but still people I don't know.  I don't mind that, but I would like to know where and how you found this LJ.  So if you place a comment here, just add the how and where. ;)
Thanks a bunch!

Great weekend!
Korn and Fantomas for two nights in a row and a great family trip to one of the most beautiful places here in Iceland.

I must be getting old because two nights in a row of slamming/moshing/screaming/jumping has left me feeling like an 80 year old or something.  My body aches all over and I have quite a few bruises, but damn, it was sooo worth it.

I just came back home from my niece's birthday party.  I think I ate too many cakes because I feel nauseous.

That is all
